{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775887085500,"sessionID":"ses_284e1b66dffed0htFjvM7NnZ96","part":{"id":"prt_d7b1e6acc001wTe8cPnaXavLeg","messageID":"msg_d7b1e5cde001L6FR1Z3frhTlsx","sessionID":"ses_284e1b66dffed0htFjvM7NnZ96","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_4d7994fef45440038eb59c6f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-042 — Docusaurus Documentation Site Framework\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Establish a Docusaurus-based documentation site framework for the agentcube project to provide a modern, searchable, and versioned documentation platform. This framework will enable the team to maintain comprehensive documentation including API references, tutorials, architecture guides, and contributor guidelines in a scalable and maintainable manner.\n6: \n7: ## Scope\n8: \n9: ### In scope\n10: \n11: | Item | Detail |\n12: |------|--------|\n13: | **Module path** | `docs` |\n14: | **Language** | TypeScript |\n15: | **Framework** | Docusaurus 3.x |\n16: | **Documentation types** | API docs, guides, tutorials, changelog, blog |\n17: | **Versioning** | Multi-version support for releases |\n18: | **Deployment target** | Static site generation for GitHub Pages or similar |\n19: \n20: ### Out of scope\n21: \n22: - Content authoring for specific documentation pages\n23: - CI/CD pipeline integration for deployment\n24: - Search backend configuration (Algolia DocSearch)\n25: - Custom React components beyond Docusaurus defaults\n26: - Internationalization (i18n) setup\n27: - Translation workflows\n28: \n29: ### Dependencies\n30: \n31: | Dependency | Usage |\n32: |------------|-------|\n33: | `docusaurus` | Core documentation framework |\n34: | `@docusaurus/preset-classic` | Classic preset with docs, blog, pages |\n35: | `@docusaurus/theme-classic` | Default theme |\n36: | `@mdx-js/react` | MDX support for React in Markdown |\n37: | `react`, `react-dom` | UI library |\n38: \n39: ## Design\n40: \n41: ### Directory structure\n42: \n43: ```\n44: docs/\n45: ├── docusaurus.config.ts          # Docusaurus configuration\n46: ├── sidebars.ts                    # Sidebar configuration\n47: ├── tsconfig.json                  # TypeScript configuration\n48: ├── package.json                   # Node dependencies\n49: ├── package-lock.json\n50: ├── static/                        # Static assets\n51: │   ├── img/                       # Images\n52: │   └── favicon.ico\n53: ├── docs/                          # Documentation files (Markdown/MDX)\n54: │   ├── index.md                   # Landing page\n55: │   ├── getting-started/          # Getting started guides\n56: │   ├── guides/                    # User guides\n57: │   ├── api/                       # API reference\n58: │   └── contributed/               # Contributor guidelines\n59: ├── blog/                          # Blog posts (optional)\n60: │   └── index.md\n61: ├── src/                           # Custom React components\n62: │   ├── css/\n63: │   │   └── custom.css            # Custom styles\n64: │   └── pages/                    # Custom pages\n65: │       └── index.tsx             # Landing page component\n66: ├── versioned_docs/                # Versioned documentation\n67: │   └── version-1.0.0/\n68: ├── versioned_sidebars/            # Sidebars for versions\n69: └── scripts/                      # Build/deploy scripts\n70:     └── build.sh\n71: ```\n72: \n73: ### Docusaurus configuration\n74: \n75: ```typescript\n76: // docusaurus.config.ts\n77: import { themes as prismThemes } from 'prism-react-renderer';\n78: import type { Config } from '@docusaurus/types';\n79: import type * as Preset from '@docusaurus/preset-classic';\n80: \n81: const config: Config = {\n82:   title: 'AgentCube',\n83:   tagline: 'Intelligent Agent Runtime Platform',\n84:   url: 'https://agentcube.io',\n85:   baseUrl: '/',\n86:   onBrokenLinks: 'throw',\n87:   onBrokenMarkdownLinks: 'warn',\n88:   favicon: 'img/favicon.ico',\n89:   organizationName: 'volcano-sh',\n90:   projectName: 'agentcube',\n91: \n92:   presets: [\n93:     [\n94:       'classic',\n95:       {\n96:         docs: {\n97:           sidebarPath: './sidebars.ts',\n98:           docVersionSuggestions: true,\n99:           showLastUpdateAuthor: true,\n100:           showLastUpdateTime: true,\n101:         },\n102:         blog: {\n103:           showReadingTime: true,\n104:           blogSidebarCount: 'ALL',\n105:           blogSidebarTitle: 'All Posts',\n106:         },\n107:         theme: {\n108:           customCss: './src/css/custom.css',\n109:         },\n110:       } satisfies Preset.Options,\n111:     ],\n112:   ],\n113: \n114:   themeConfig: {\n115:     image: 'img/social-card.png',\n116:     navbar: {\n117:       title: 'AgentCube',\n118:       logo: {\n119:         alt: 'AgentCube Logo',\n120:         src: 'img/logo.svg',\n121:       },\n122:       items: [\n123:         {\n124:           type: 'docSidebar',\n125:           sidebarId: 'docsSidebar',\n126:           position: 'left',\n127:           label: 'Docs',\n128:         },\n129:         {\n130:           type: 'docsVersionDropdown',\n131:           position: 'right',\n132:         },\n133:         {\n134:           href: 'https://github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube',\n135:           label: 'GitHub',\n136:           position: 'right',\n137:         },\n138:       ],\n139:     },\n140:     footer: {\n141:       style: 'dark',\n142:       copyright: `Copyright © ${new Date().getFullYear()} Volcano.sh`,\n143:     },\n144:     prism: {\n145:       theme: prismThemes.github,\n146:       darkTheme: prismThemes.dracula,\n147:     },\n148:   } satisfies Preset.ThemeConfig,\n149: };\n150: \n151: export default config;\n152: ```\n153: \n154: ### Sidebar configuration\n155: \n156: ```typescript\n157: // sidebars.ts\n158: import type { SidebarsConfig } from '@docusaurus/plugin-content-docs';\n159: \n160: const sidebars: SidebarsConfig = {\n161:   docsSidebar: [\n162:     'intro',\n163:     {\n164:       type: 'category',\n165:       label: 'Getting Started',\n166:       collapsed: false,\n167:       items: ['getting-started/installation', 'getting-started/quickstart'],\n168:     },\n169:     {\n170:       type: 'category',\n171:       label: 'Guides',\n172:       items: [\n173:         'guides/architecture',\n174:         'guides/configuration',\n175:         'guides/monitoring',\n176:       ],\n177:     },\n178:     {\n179:       type: 'category',\n180:       label: 'API Reference',\n181:       items: [\n182:         'api/agent-runtime',\n183:         'api/code-interpreter',\n184:         'api/cli',\n185:       ],\n186:     },\n187:     {\n188:       type: 'category',\n189:       label: 'Contributing',\n190:       items: [\n191:         'contributed/overview',\n192:         'contributed/development',\n193:         'contributed/coding-standards',\n194:       ],\n195:     },\n196:   ],\n197: };\n198: \n199: export default sidebars;\n200: ```\n201: \n202: ### Package.json scripts\n203: \n204: ```json\n205: {\n206:   \"scripts\": {\n207:     \"docusaurus\": \"docusaurus\",\n208:     \"start\": \"docusaurus start\",\n209:     \"build\": \"docusaurus build\",\n210:     \"deploy\": \"docusaurus deploy\",\n211:     \"clear\": \"docusaurus clear\",\n212:     \"serve\": \"docusaurus serve\",\n213:     \"write-translations\": \"docusaurus write-translations\",\n214:     \"write-heading-ids\": \"docusaurus write-heading-ids\"\n215:   }\n216: }\n217: ```\n218: \n219: ### Custom CSS example\n220: \n221: ```css\n222: /* src/css/custom.css */\n223: :root {\n224:   --ifm-color-primary: #3b82f6;\n225:   --ifm-color-primary-dark: #2563eb;\n226:   --ifm-color-primary-darker: #1d4ed8;\n227:   --ifm-color-primary-darkest: #1e40af;\n228:   --ifm-color-primary-light: #60a5fa;\n229:   --ifm-color-primary-lighter: #93c5fd;\n230:   --ifm-color-primary-lightest: #bfdbfe;\n231:   --ifm-code-font-size: 95%;\n232: }\n233: \n234: .navbar__title {\n235:   font-weight: 700;\n236: }\n237: \n238: .admonition {\n239:   font-size: 0.9rem;\n240: }\n241: ```\n242: \n243: ## Impact analysis\n244: \n245: ### Files created\n246: \n247: | File | Description |\n248: |------|-------------|\n249: | `docs/docusaurus.config.ts` | Docusaurus configuration (~80 lines) |\n250: | `docs/sidebars.ts` | Sidebar navigation config (~40 lines) |\n251: | `docs/tsconfig.json` | TypeScript config (~20 lines) |\n252: | `docs/package.json` | Node dependencies (~40 lines) |\n253: | `docs/package-lock.json` | Lock file |\n254: | `docs/static/*` | Static assets (~5 files) |\n255: | `docs/docs/intro.md` | Introduction page (~30 lines) |\n256: | `docs/docs/getting-started/*.md` | Getting started guides (~100 lines) |\n257: | `docs/docs/guides/*.md` | User guides (~150 lines) |\n258: | `docs/docs/api/*.md` | API reference templates (~100 lines) |\n259: | `docs/docs/contributed/*.md` | Contributor guidelines (~100 lines) |\n260: | `docs/src/css/custom.css` | Custom styles (~50 lines) |\n261: | `docs/src/pages/index.tsx` | Landing page (~80 lines) |\n262: \n263: **Estimated total**: ~800 lines\n264: \n265: ### Files modified\n266: \n267: | File | Change |\n268: |------|--------|\n269: | `.gitignore` | Add docs/build, docs/node_modules |\n270: | `README.md` | Add docs site link |\n271: \n272: ### Dependencies\n273: \n274: | Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n275: |------------|---------|---------|\n276: | @docusaurus/core | ^3.0.0 | Core framework |\n277: | @docusaurus/preset-classic | ^3.0.0 | Preset with docs/blog |\n278: | @docusaurus/theme-classic | ^3.0.0 | Default theme |\n279: | @mdx-js/react | ^3.0.0 | MDX support |\n280: | react | ^18.2.0 | React library |\n281: | react-dom | ^18.2.0 | React DOM |\n282: \n283: ### Downstream consumers\n284: \n285: | Consumer | Dependency |\n286: |----------|-----------|\n287: | Developers | Use docs for onboarding and reference |\n288: | Users | Self-service documentation |\n289: | Support team | Reference for troubleshooting |\n290: | Marketing | Product documentation |\n291: \n292: ### Breaking change risk\n293: \n294: **Very Low**: This is a new documentation module. No existing code is modified. The documentation site is additive and does not affect the core product functionality.\n295: \n296: ### Performance characteristics\n297: \n298: - **Build time**: ~1-3 minutes for full site\n299: - **Dev server startup**: ~10-20 seconds\n300: - **Static site size**: ~10-50MB depending on content\n301: - **Page load**: Fast with static generation + optional CDN\n302: \n303: ### Edge cases handled\n304: \n305: 1. **Broken links**: Docusaurus validates links during build\n306: 2. **Missing images**: Graceful fallback for missing assets\n307: 3. **Version conflicts**: Explicit version management\n308: 4. **Build failures**: Clear error messages for authoring issues\n309: 5. **Mobile responsiveness**: Built-in responsive design\n310: \n311: ## Alternatives considered\n312: \n313: ### 1. Use GitBook\n314: \n315: **Approach**: Use GitBook platform for documentation.\n316: \n317: **Rejected because**:\n318: - Proprietary SaaS with limited customization\n319: - Free tier restrictions on collaborators\n320: - Less control over hosting and branding\n321: - Integration requires GitHub OAuth\n322: \n323: ### 2. Use MkDocs with Material theme\n324: \n325: **Approach**: Use MkDocs (Python) with Material for MkDocs theme.\n326: \n327: **Rejected because**:\n328: - Python-based (team more familiar with Node.js/TypeScript)\n329: - MDX not supported natively (limited React component embedding)\n330: - Static site generation less flexible for React integrations\n331: - Team preference for JavaScript ecosystem\n332: \n333: ### 3. Use VuePress / VitePress\n334: \n335: **Approach**: Use VuePress or VitePress (Vue-based documentation frameworks).\n336: \n337: **Rejected because**:\n338: - Vue ecosystem (team works with React)\n339: - Docusaurus has better integration with React-based projects\n340: - Docusaurus has mature multi-version support\n341: - Docusaurus is the standard for Meta/Facebook ecosystem projects\n342: \n343: ### 4. Use plain Markdown with GitHub Pages\n344: \n345: **Approach**: Use raw Markdown files with GitHub Pages (Jekyll).\n346: \n347: **Rejected because**:\n348: - Limited navigation and search functionality\n349: - No built-in versioning support\n350: - Poor mobile experience\n351: - Manual navigation structure management\n352: - No React component support in MDX\n353: \n354: ### 5. Use Next.js with next-mdx-remote\n355: \n356: **Approach**: Build custom docs site with Next.js and MDX.\n357: \n358: **Rejected because**:\n359: - Significant development overhead\n360: - Custom implementation required for features Docusaurus provides out-of-box\n361: - Higher maintenance burden\n362: - Versioning requires custom implementation\n363: - Team preference for purpose-built solution\n364: \n365: ### 6. Use Hugo with Docsy theme\n366: \n367: **Approach**: Use Hugo static site generator with Docsy theme.\n368: \n369: **Rejected because**:\n370: - Go template ecosystem (team not familiar with)\n371: - MDX support limited\n372: - Less React integration capability\n373: - More complex theming customization\n\n(End of file - total 373 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-042 — Docusaurus Documentation Site Framework\n\n## Purpose\n\nEstablish a Docusaurus-based documentation site framework for the agentcube project to provide a modern, searchable, and versioned documentation platform. This framework will enable the team to maintain comprehensive documentation including API references, tutorials, architecture guides, and contributor guidelines in a scalable and maintainable manner.\n\n## Scope\n\n### In scope\n\n| Item | Detail |\n|------|--------|\n| **Module path** | `docs` |\n| **Language** | TypeScript |\n| **Framework** | Docusaurus 3.x |\n| **Documentation types** | API docs, guides, tutorials, changelog, blog |\n| **Versioning** | Multi-version support for releases |\n| **Deployment target** | Static site generation for GitHub Pages or similar |\n\n### Out of scope","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775887085473,"end":1775887085497}}}}
