{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775887110332,"sessionID":"ses_284e1b66dffed0htFjvM7NnZ96","part":{"id":"prt_d7b1ecd2c001f8ALusO7oJlGJg","messageID":"msg_d7b1ebc72001oFfYI5s4AjYtbj","sessionID":"ses_284e1b66dffed0htFjvM7NnZ96","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_9bab06ba663a460993787678","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/docs/docs/api/agent-runtime.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/docs/docs/api/agent-runtime.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: id: agent-runtime\n3: title: Agent Runtime API\n4: description: Agent Runtime API reference\n5: sidebar_position: 1\n6: ---\n7: \n8: # Agent Runtime API\n9: \n10: The Agent Runtime API provides programmatic access to agent management and execution.\n11: \n12: ## Base URL\n13: \n14: ```\n15: http://localhost:8080/api/v1\n16: ```\n17: \n18: ## Authentication\n19: \n20: All API requests require an API key in the header:\n21: \n22: ```bash\n23: curl -H \"Authorization: Bearer YOUR_API_KEY\" ...\n24: ```\n25: \n26: ## Endpoints\n27: \n28: ### Create Agent\n29: \n30: Create a new agent.\n31: \n32: ```http\n33: POST /agents\n34: ```\n35: \n36: **Request Body:**\n37: \n38: ```json\n39: {\n40:   \"name\": \"my-agent\",\n41:   \"description\": \"A helpful assistant\",\n42:   \"model\": \"gpt-4\",\n43:   \"instructions\": \"You are a helpful assistant.\",\n44:   \"tools\": [\"code-interpreter\", \"web-search\"],\n45:   \"metadata\": {\n46:     \"team\": \"engineering\"\n47:   }\n48: }\n49: ```\n50: \n51: **Response:**\n52: \n53: ```json\n54: {\n55:   \"id\": \"agent_abc123\",\n56:   \"name\": \"my-agent\",\n57:   \"status\": \"active\",\n58:   \"created_at\": \"2024-01-15T10:30:00Z\"\n59: }\n60: ```\n61: \n62: ### Get Agent\n63: \n64: Retrieve agent details.\n65: \n66: ```http\n67: GET /agents/{agent_id}\n68: ```\n69: \n70: **Response:**\n71: \n72: ```json\n73: {\n74:   \"id\": \"agent_abc123\",\n75:   \"name\": \"my-agent\",\n76:   \"description\": \"A helpful assistant\",\n77:   \"model\": \"gpt-4\",\n78:   \"status\": \"active\",\n79:   \"created_at\": \"2024-01-15T10:30:00Z\",\n80:   \"updated_at\": \"2024-01-15T10:30:00Z\"\n81: }\n82: ```\n83: \n84: ### List Agents\n85: \n86: List all agents.\n87: \n88: ```http\n89: GET /agents\n90: ```\n91: \n92: **Query Parameters:**\n93: \n94: | Parameter | Type | Description |\n95: |-----------|------|-------------|\n96: | `limit` | int | Max results (default: 20) |\n97: | `offset` | int | Pagination offset |\n98: | `status` | string | Filter by status |\n99: \n100: **Response:**\n101: \n102: ```json\n103: {\n104:   \"agents\": [\n105:     {\n106:       \"id\": \"agent_abc123\",\n107:       \"name\": \"my-agent\",\n108:       \"status\": \"active\"\n109:     }\n110:   ],\n111:   \"total\": 1\n112: }\n113: ```\n114: \n115: ### Update Agent\n116: \n117: Update an existing agent.\n118: \n119: ```http\n120: PATCH /agents/{agent_id}\n121: ```\n122: \n123: **Request Body:**\n124: \n125: ```json\n126: {\n127:   \"instructions\": \"You are a helpful coding assistant.\",\n128:   \"tools\": [\"code-interpreter\"]\n129: }\n130: ```\n131: \n132: ### Delete Agent\n133: \n134: Delete an agent.\n135: \n136: ```http\n137: DELETE /agents/{agent_id}\n138: ```\n139: \n140: **Response:** `204 No Content`\n141: \n142: ### Invoke Agent\n143: \n144: Invoke an agent to process a request.\n145: \n146: ```http\n147: POST /agents/{agent_id}/invoke\n148: ```\n149: \n150: **Request Body:**\n151: \n152: ```json\n153: {\n154:   \"message\": \"Hello, how are you?\",\n155:   \"session_id\": \"session_abc123\",\n156:   \"stream\": false,\n157:   \"context\": {}\n158: }\n159: ```\n160: \n161: **Response:**\n162: \n163: ```json\n164: {\n165:   \"response\": \"I'm doing well, thank you!\",\n166:   \"session_id\": \"session_abc123\",\n167:   \"usage\": {\n168:     \"input_tokens\": 10,\n169:     \"output_tokens\": 15,\n170:     \"total_tokens\": 25\n171:   }\n172: }\n173: ```\n174: \n175: ### Stream Invoke\n176: \n177: Invoke an agent with streaming response.\n178: \n179: ```http\n180: POST /agents/{agent_id}/invoke\n181: ```\n182: \n183: **Request Body:**\n184: \n185: ```json\n186: {\n187:   \"message\": \"Write a story\",\n188:   \"stream\": true\n189: }\n190: ```\n191: \n192: **Response (Server-Sent Events):**\n193: \n194: ```stream\n195: data: {\"chunk\": \"Once\", \"done\": false}\n196: data: {\"chunk\": \" upon\", \"done\": false}\n197: data: {\"chunk\": \" a time\", \"done\": false}\n198: data: {\"done\": true}\n199: ```\n200: \n201: ## Types\n202: \n203: ### Agent\n204: \n205: ```typescript\n206: interface Agent {\n207:   id: string;\n208:   name: string;\n209:   description?: string;\n210:   model: string;\n211:   instructions: string;\n212:   tools: string[];\n213:   metadata: Record<string, string>;\n214:   status: 'active' | 'paused' | 'deleted';\n215:   created_at: string;\n216:   updated_at: string;\n217: }\n218: ```\n219: \n220: ### InvocationRequest\n221: \n222: ```typescript\n223: interface InvocationRequest {\n224:   message: string;\n225:   session_id?: string;\n226:   stream?: boolean;\n227:   context?: Record<string, unknown>;\n228:   temperature?: number;\n229:   max_tokens?: number;\n230: }\n231: ```\n232: \n233: ### InvocationResponse\n234: \n235: ```typescript\n236: interface InvocationResponse {\n237:   response: string;\n238:   session_id: string;\n239:   usage: {\n240:     input_tokens: number;\n241:     output_tokens: number;\n242:     total_tokens: number;\n243:   };\n244:   metadata?: Record<string, unknown>;\n245: }\n246: ```\n247: \n248: ## Error Codes\n249: \n250: | Code | Description |\n251: |------|-------------|\n252: | `400` | Bad Request |\n253: | `401` | Unauthorized |\n254: | `404` | Agent Not Found |\n255: | `429` | Rate Limited |\n256: | `500` | Internal Server Error |\n257: | `503` | Service Unavailable |\n258: \n259: ## Rate Limits\n260: \n261: - **Standard**: 60 requests/minute\n262: - **Pro**: 600 requests/minute\n263: - **Enterprise**: Custom\n264: \n265: ## SDK Examples\n266: \n267: ### Python\n268: \n269: ```python\n270: from agentcube import AgentRuntime\n271: \n272: client = AgentRuntime(api_key=\"YOUR_API_KEY\")\n273: \n274: response = client.invoke(\n275:     agent_id=\"agent_abc123\",\n276:     message=\"Hello!\"\n277: )\n278: print(response.response)\n279: ```\n280: \n281: ### JavaScript\n282: \n283: ```javascript\n284: import { AgentRuntime } from '@agentcube/sdk';\n285: \n286: const client = new AgentRuntime({ apiKey: 'YOUR_API_KEY' });\n287: \n288: const response = await client.invoke({\n289:   agentId: 'agent_abc123',\n290:   message: 'Hello!'\n291: });\n292: \n293: console.log(response.response);\n294: ```\n295: \n296: ## Next Steps\n297: \n298: - [Code Interpreter API](/docs/api/code-interpreter)\n299: - [CLI Reference](/docs/api/cli)\n\n(End of file - total 299 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\nid: agent-runtime\ntitle: Agent Runtime API\ndescription: Agent Runtime API reference\nsidebar_position: 1\n---\n\n# Agent Runtime API\n\nThe Agent Runtime API provides programmatic access to agent management and execution.\n\n## Base URL\n\n```\nhttp://localhost:8080/api/v1\n```\n\n## Authentication\n\nAll API requests require an API key in the header:","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/docs/docs/api/agent-runtime.md","time":{"start":1775887110321,"end":1775887110329}}}}
