{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775887148516,"sessionID":"ses_284e1b66dffed0htFjvM7NnZ96","part":{"id":"prt_d7b1ee2270013Mz7ThqNsRWJH4","messageID":"msg_d7b1ed0ed001rgTxZhvTV1nFws","sessionID":"ses_284e1b66dffed0htFjvM7NnZ96","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_4b7fec4c0dcf42a9883635e5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-043 — 架构设计文档与 API 文档\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe purpose of this proposal is to create comprehensive architecture design documentation and API documentation for the AgentCube project. This documentation will:\n\n1. Provide detailed architectural diagrams and component descriptions for the SDK and runtime system\n2. Document all public APIs for the Python SDK, including client classes, services, and CLI commands\n3. Establish a single source of truth for developers integrating with AgentCube\n4. Enable faster onboarding for new team members and external developers\n5. Support the existing Docusaurus documentation framework established in AR-042\n\n## Scope\n\n### In scope\n\n| Item | Detail |\n|------|--------|\n| **Module path** | `docs` |\n| **Language** | Markdown (via Docusaurus) |\n| **Documentation type** | Architecture design + API reference |\n\n### Architectural Documentation\n\n| Document | Description |\n|----------|-------------|\n| `docs/docs/architecture/system-design.md` | System-level architecture with component interactions |\n| `docs/docs/architecture/client-sdk.md` | SDK client architecture (AgentRuntimeClient, CodeInterpreterClient) |\n| `docs/docs/architecture/services.md` | Service layer architecture (MetadataService, DockerService, K8sProvider) |\n| `docs/docs/architecture/runtime.md` | Runtime operations architecture (Pack, Build, Publish, Invoke, Status) |\n| `docs/docs/architecture/data-flow.md` | Data flow diagrams and sequence diagrams |\n\n### API Documentation\n\n| Document | Description |\n|----------|-------------|\n| `docs/docs/api/sdk-agent-runtime.md` | AgentRuntimeClient SDK API |\n| `docs/docs/api/sdk-code-interpreter.md` | CodeInterpreterClient SDK API |\n| `docs/docs/api/sdk-services.md` | Service layer APIs |\n| `docs/docs/api/sdk-runtime.md` | Runtime operation APIs |\n| `docs/docs/api/sdk-exceptions.md` | Exception reference |\n| `docs/docs/api/sdk-cli.md` | CLI command reference |\n\n### Out of scope\n\n- Backend API documentation (Router, Control Plane, Data Plane endpoints)\n- Deployment and infrastructure documentation\n- User guides and tutorials (covered in existing docs)\n- Internal implementation details not exposed via public API\n\n### Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Usage |\n|------------|-------|\n| Docusaurus 3.x | Documentation framework (from AR-042) |\n| Existing `docs/docs/guides/architecture.md` | Current architecture content to be expanded |\n| Existing `docs/docs/api/*` | Current API docs to be replaced/enhanced |\n| Mermaid.js | Diagram rendering in Markdown |\n\n## Design\n\n### Directory structure additions\n\n```\ndocs/\n└── docs/\n    ├── architecture/           # New architecture docs\n    │   ├── system-design.md\n    │   ├── client-sdk.md\n    │   ├── services.md\n    │   ├── runtime.md\n    │   └── data-flow.md\n    └── api/\n        ├── sdk-agent-runtime.md\n        ├── sdk-code-interpreter.md\n        ├── sdk-services.md\n        ├── sdk-runtime.md\n        ├── sdk-exceptions.md\n        └── sdk-cli.md\n```\n\n### Architecture documentation format\n\n```markdown\n# Component Name\n\n## Overview\n\nBrief description of the component's purpose and responsibilities.\n\n## Architecture Diagram\n\n```mermaid\ngraph TB\n    A[Client] --> B[Router]\n    B --> C[Agent Runtime]\n```\n\n## Key Classes/Functions\n\n### ClassName\n\n| Property/Method | Type | Description |\n|-----------------|------|-------------|\n| `param` | `str` | Description |\n\n## Initialization\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube import ClassName\n\nclient = ClassName(param=\"value\")\n```\n\n## Use Cases\n\n1. Use case 1\n2. Use case 2\n```\n\n### API documentation format\n\n```markdown\n# SDK API Reference\n\n## ClassName\n\n### Constructor\n\n```python\nClassName(param1: str, param2: int = 10)\n```\n\n| Parameter | Type | Default | Description |\n|-----------|------|---------|-------------|\n| param1 | str | Required | Description |\n\n### Methods\n\n#### method_name\n\n```python\nclient.method_name(arg1: str) -> dict\n```\n\n**Parameters:**\n\n| Name | Type | Description |\n|------|------|-------------|\n| arg1 | str | Description |\n\n**Returns:** `dict` - Description\n\n**Raises:** `ExceptionType` - When condition\n\n**Example:**\n\n```python\nresult = client.method_name(\"value\")\n```\n\n## Exceptions\n\n| Exception | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `AgentCubeError` | Base exception |\n```\n\n### Sidebar updates\n\n```typescript\n// sidebars.ts addition\n{\n  type: 'category',\n  label: 'Architecture',\n  items: [\n    'architecture/system-design',\n    'architecture/client-sdk',\n    'architecture/services',\n    'architecture/runtime',\n    'architecture/data-flow',\n  ],\n},\n{\n  type: 'category',\n  label: 'SDK API Reference',\n  items: [\n    'api/sdk-agent-runtime',\n    'api/sdk-code-interpreter',\n    'api/sdk-services',\n    'api/sdk-runtime',\n    'api/sdk-exceptions',\n    'api/sdk-cli',\n  ],\n},\n```\n\n## Impact analysis\n\n### Files created\n\n| File | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `docs/docs/architecture/system-design.md` | System architecture (~150 lines) |\n| `docs/docs/architecture/client-sdk.md` | SDK client architecture (~200 lines) |\n| `docs/docs/architecture/services.md` | Services architecture (~150 lines) |\n| `docs/docs/architecture/runtime.md` | Runtime operations (~150 lines) |\n| `docs/docs/architecture/data-flow.md` | Data flow diagrams (~100 lines) |\n| `docs/docs/api/sdk-agent-runtime.md` | AgentRuntimeClient API (~250 lines) |\n| `docs/docs/api/sdk-code-interpreter.md` | CodeInterpreterClient API (~300 lines) |\n| `docs/docs/api/sdk-services.md` | Services API (~200 lines) |\n| `docs/docs/api/sdk-runtime.md` | Runtime API (~200 lines) |\n| `docs/docs/api/sdk-exceptions.md` | Exceptions reference (~100 lines) |\n| `docs/docs/api/sdk-cli.md` | CLI reference (~200 lines) |\n\n**Estimated total**: ~1800 lines\n\n### Files modified\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `docs/sidebars.ts` | Add architecture and SDK API categories |\n| `docs/docusaurus.config.ts` | Add Mermaid support if needed |\n\n### Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n|------------|---------|---------|\n| mermaid | ^10.0.0 | Diagram rendering |\n| @docusaurus/theme-mermaid | ^3.0.0 | Mermaid plugin for Docusaurus |\n\n### Downstream consumers\n\n| Consumer | Dependency |\n|----------|-----------|\n| SDK users | Reference for integration |\n| Internal developers | Understanding architecture |\n| External contributors | Onboarding and contribution |\n| Technical writers | Maintain documentation |\n\n### Breaking change risk\n\n**Very Low**: This is documentation-only work. No code changes are made. Existing documentation remains accessible alongside new content.\n\n### Performance characteristics\n\n- **Build time impact**: Minimal (~5-10 seconds for new docs)\n- **Static site size**: ~1-2MB additional for diagrams\n- **Rendering**: Mermaid diagrams render client-side\n\n### Edge cases handled\n\n1. **Missing diagrams**: Graceful fallback with link to source\n2. **Code examples**: Tested against actual SDK code\n3. **API changes**: Documentation follows code conventions from source\n4. **Cross-references**: Internal links between related docs\n\n## Alternatives considered\n\n### 1. Auto-generate from docstrings using pdoc/sphinx\n\n**Approach**: Use automated documentation generation from Python docstrings.\n\n**Rejected because**:\n- Generates API reference only, no architectural overview\n- Doesn't integrate with Docusaurus theme\n- Limited customization for different audiences\n- Requires additional tooling setup\n\n### 2. Use OpenAPI/Swagger for API docs\n\n**Approach**: Define API contracts in OpenAPI spec and generate docs.\n\n**Rejected because**:\n- Primary API is Python SDK, not HTTP REST\n- CLI docs not covered by OpenAPI\n- Additional infrastructure needed for spec management\n- Less readable for SDK users\n\n### 3. Use TypeDoc for JavaScript SDK documentation\n\n**Approach**: Use TypeDoc for generating JavaScript-focused API docs.\n\n**Rejected because**:\n- AgentCube SDK is Python-based\n- Doesn't integrate with existing Docusaurus\n- No support for architecture diagrams\n- Different audience from TypeScript developers\n\n### 4. Use Sphinx with Read the Docs\n\n**Approach**: Use Sphinx (Python documentation tool) with Read the Docs.\n\n**Rejected because**:\n- Duplicates documentation framework (Docusaurus from AR-042)\n- Team expertise in Docusaurus/MDX\n- Less flexible theming\n- Multiple documentation sites\n\n### 5. Focus only on REST API documentation\n\n**Approach**: Document only the HTTP API, not SDK.\n\n**Rejected because**:\n- Primary integration point is Python SDK\n- SDK provides better developer experience\n- CLI needs separate documentation\n- Incomplete coverage for users","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/agentcube/agent_runtime.py\">\nERROR [147:62] Type \"int | tuple[float, float] | None\" is not assignable to declared type \"int | tuple[float, float]\"\n  Type \"int | tuple[float, float] | None\" is not assignable to type \"int | tuple[float, float]\"\n    Type \"None\" is not assignable to type \"int | tuple[float, float]\"\n      \"None\" is not assignable to \"int\"\n      \"None\" is not assignable to \"tuple[float, float]\"\nERROR [153:31] \"invoke\" is not a known attribute of \"